Program 14 – Deploy Android Application

Step 1: Open the Project
Open Android Studio.
Open the Android project you want to deploy.

Step 2: Build the Application
Click Build → Build APK(s).
Wait until the build is completed.

Step 3: Locate the APK
The APK file is generated at:

app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk

or

app/build/outputs/apk/release/app-release.apk


Step 4: Enable USB Debugging
On your Android phone:

Open Settings.
Go to About Phone.
Tap Build Number 7 times to enable Developer Options.
Open Developer Options.
Enable USB Debugging.


Step 5: Connect Device
Connect the Android phone using a USB cable.
Allow the USB debugging permission on the phone.


Step 6: Run the Application

In Android Studio:

Click the Run (▶) button.
Select your connected device.
Click OK.

The application will be installed and launched on the device.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step 7: Generate Signed APK (Optional)

For publishing the application:

Click Build → Generate Signed Bundle / APK.
Select APK.
Create or choose a Keystore.
Enter the password and key alias.
Select Release.
Click Finish.

